Hi cocos2d-x team. 

I'm using cocos2d-x for my 2D platformer project. And the camera system very usefull instead of the parallax system. (believe me) I always use the camera for the player following, backgrounds...etc I'm setting background positions negative values for depth feeling just like that;   

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YlM6goPZmpU&feature=youtu.be&t=9s

But If I set background z positions as negative values , my background sprites are getting smaller as the size. I don't want to that, because I prepare graphics with original size and some graphics are deforming. 

I think this feature would be very nice!

```
mySprite->setPositionZ(-100);
//and I'm setting fixed size property with like that
mySprite->setDisablePerspectiveSizeFactor(true);
```

Please add that feature in the next version and it's really important feature for me. :( I'm working to do that with crazy hack methods for now. :(((

Thank you.
